ificity issues.*.",[56,838,839],{},"Just a breath of fresh air.",[56,841,842],{},"Even with one style per line for readability I have managed to shrink the file size of ALL the components I converted.",[56,844,845,846,851],{},"I only now have two sections to worry about now, the logic, and the presentation. I've come to understand that presentation is invariably linked to state, and separating the css actually always makes things more painful. The creator of tailwind actually mentions this in the ",[69,847,850],{"href":848,"rel":849},"https://adamwathan.me/css-utility-classes-and-separation-of-concerns/",[73],"blog post"," where he made the arguments for tailwind on it's release, and I had read this before, but it never sunk in how painful this was until I wasn't experiencing the pain anymore.",[56,853,854,855,153],{},"I was actually surprised how much faster I could style things (~3x) even when I had to have the tailwind docs pinned to lookup stuff and my tailwind autocomplete was not working well",[126,856,857],{},[69,858,862],{"href":859,"ariaDescribedBy":860,"dataFootnoteRef":133,"id":861},"#user-content-fn-2",[132],"user-content-fnref-2","2",[56,864,865],{},"I've come to appreciate how easy it can do things that used to take multiple lines.",[56,867,868,869,876],{},"Take for example ",[69,870,873],{"href":871,"rel":872},"https://tailwindcss.com/docs/text-overflow#truncate",[73],[92,874,875],{},"truncate"," which does:",[138,878,883],{"className":879,"code":881,"language":882},[880],"language-text","overflow: hidden;\ntext-overflow: ellipsis;\nwhite-space: nowrap;\n","text",[92,884,881],{"__ignoreMap":133},[56,886,887],{},"Or gradients! If there's one thing I hate, it's writing css gradients. But in tailwind it's super simple, even with complex stops and everything:",[138,889,891],{"className":479,"code":890,"language":481,"meta":133,"style":133},"\u003Cdiv class=\"bg-gradient-to-r from-white to-black\"/>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"\n    bg-gradient-to-r\n    from-white from-10%\n    via-blue-500 via-20%\n    to-black to-50%\n\"/>\n",[92,892,893,912,924,929,934,939,944],{"__ignoreMap":133},[146,894,895,897,899,901,903,905,908,910],{"class":148,"line":149},[146,896,488],{"class":152},[146,898,525],{"class":491},[146,900,528],{"class":263},[146,902,503],{"class":152},[146,904,506],{"class":152},[146,906,907],{"class":535},"bg-gradient-to-r from-white to-black",[146,909,506],{"class":152},[146,911,541],{"class":152},[146,913,914,916,918,920,922],{"class":148,"line":163},[146,915,488],{"class":152},[146,917,525],{"class":491},[146,919,528],{"class":263},[146,921,503],{"class":152},[146,923,512],{"class":152},[146,925,926],{"class":148,"line":191},[146,927,928],{"class":535},"    bg-gradient-to-r\n",[146,930,931],{"class":148,"line":212},[146,932,933],{"class":535},"    from-white from-10%\n",[146,935,936],{"class":148,"line":225},[146,937,938],{"class":535},"    via-blue-500 via-20%\n",[146,940,941],{"class":148,"line":255},[146,942,943],{"class":535},"    to-black to-50%\n",[146,945,946,948],{"class":148,"line":287},[146,947,506],{"class":152},[146,949,541],{"class":152},[951,952,954],"h2",{"id":953},"tailwind-merge","* Tailwind Merge",[56,956,957],{},"But, tailwind merge is a MUST for complex applications and component libraries to avoid specificity issues. The reason why is that while tailwind cannot escape the css selector specificity problem completely, in fact we loose a bit of control.",[56,959,960],{},"See in regular css, if I have two selectors with equal specificity, the last one will win (note that this helps avoid the mess of having many variants and states):",[138,962,965],{"className":963,"code":964,"language":123,"meta":133,"style":133},"language-css shiki shiki-themes material-theme-lighter material-theme material-theme-palenight",".input {\n    &.border:focus {...}\n    &.disabled:focus {...}\n}\n",[92,966,967,976,990,1009],{"__ignoreMap":133},[146,968,969,971,974],{"class":148,"line":149},[146,970,153],{"class":152},